{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882616969,"sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","part":{"id":"prt_d7ada3e46001ACpqD8j04Z0la6","messageID":"msg_d7ada32cb0011qJNoVnDh6Al09","sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_tool-baf37ed31ea74cbf8e2658034e3e637b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"AR-031"},"output":"Found 16 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n  Line 5: AR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n  Line 316: AR-031 RBAC configuration is fully implemented and tested. All templates, configuration, and tests are in place and follow the design specification. The implementation provides:\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/design.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Design\n  Line 5: AR-031 defines the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components (controller-manager, workload-manager, router). The RBAC configuration ensures proper permission boundaries for each component while maintaining flexibility for custom deployments.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Delta Specification\n  Line 4: - **A