{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882625641,"sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","part":{"id":"prt_d7ada623f001XHCK6W6u7vQPZs","messageID":"msg_d7ada40c6001571OOtEwIx4y6O","sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bf7268ea0a434b29ae6e0618e8ab4d8d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: AR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `manifests`\n8: **Language:** YAML (Helm templates)\n9: **Status:** ✅ COMPLETE\n10: \n11: ## Implementation Details\n12: \n13: ### Files Created/Modified\n14: \n15: #### Templates (Existing)\n16: All RBAC templates were already implemented and follow the design specification:\n17: \n18: 1. **ServiceAccount Templates**\n19:    - `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n20:    - `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n21:    - `templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml`\n22: \n23: 2. **RBAC Templates**\n24:    - `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n25:    - `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` (ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:    - `templates/router/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n27: \n28: 3. **Helper Templates**\n29:    - `templates/_helpers.tpl` (ServiceAccount name helpers)\n30: \n31: #### Configuration (Existing)\n32: - `values.yaml` - Complete RBAC configuration structure\n33: \n34: #### Tests (NEW - Created in this implementation)\n35: \n36: ##### Unit Tests\n37: - `tests/rbac_test.yaml` - Comprehensive Helm template tests (24 test cases)\n38: \n39: ##### Integration Tests\n40: - `tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify workload-manager can create pods\n41: - `tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh` - Verify router can list secrets\n42: - `tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify controller-manager cannot delete pods\n43: - `tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh` - Deploy with custom RBAC rules\n44: - `tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh` - Deploy with existing ServiceAccount\n45: \n46: ##### Security Tests\n47: - `tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh` - Verify principle of least privilege\n48: - `tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh` - Check for wildcard permissions\n49: - `tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh` - Verify token automount configuration\n50: \n51: ##### Documentation\n52: - `tests/README.md` - Comprehensive test documentation\n53: \n54: ## RBAC Architecture\n55: \n56: ### Component Permissions\n57: \n58: | Component | ServiceAccount | Role/ClusterRole | Scope | Permissions |\n59: |-----------|---------------|------------------|-------|-------------|\n60: | controller-manager | `agentcube` | Role | Namespace | Custom rules (empty by default) |\n61: | workload-manager | `agentcube-workload-manager` | ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n62: | router | `agentcube-router` | Role | Namespace | Secrets (get, list, watch) |\n63: \n64: ### Workload Manager ClusterRole Rules\n65: \n66: ```yaml\n67: # CRD resources\n68: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n69:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n70:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n71: \n72: # CRD status\n73: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n74:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n75:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n76: \n77: # Core resources\n78: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n79:   resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n80:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n81: \n82: # Pod status\n83: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n84:   resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n85:   verbs: [\"get\"]\n86: \n87: # Events\n88: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n89:   resources: [\"events\"]\n90:   verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ### Router Role Rules\n94: \n95: ```yaml\n96: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n97:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n98:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Controller Manager Role Rules\n102: \n103: ```yaml\n104: # Empty by default - custom rules can be added via values.yaml\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ## Configuration Options\n108: \n109: ### Enable/Disable RBAC\n110: \n111: ```yaml\n112: controllerManager:\n113:   rbac:\n114:     create: true\n115: \n116: workloadManager:\n117:   rbac:\n118:     create: true\n119: \n120: router:\n121:   rbac:\n122:     create: true\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### Custom ServiceAccount Names\n126: \n127: ```yaml\n128: controllerManager:\n129:   serviceAccount:\n130:     name: custom-controller-sa\n131: \n132: workloadManager:\n133:   serviceAccount:\n134:     name: custom-workload-sa\n135: \n136: router:\n137:   serviceAccount:\n138:     name: custom-router-sa\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ### Use Existing ServiceAccounts\n142: \n143: ```yaml\n144: controllerManager:\n145:   serviceAccount:\n146:     create: false\n147:     name: existing-sa\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### Custom RBAC Rules\n151: \n152: ```yaml\n153: controllerManager:\n154:   rbac:\n155:     rules:\n156:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n157:         resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n158:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### ServiceAccount Annotations\n162: \n163: ```yaml\n164: controllerManager:\n165:   serviceAccount:\n166:     annotations:\n167:       eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ## Testing\n171: \n172: ### Unit Tests\n173: \n174: Run all unit tests:\n175: ```bash\n176: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Run specific test file:\n180: ```bash\n181: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -f tests/rbac_test.yaml\n182: ```\n183: \n184: **Test Coverage:**\n185: - ✅ All RBAC resources are created when enabled\n186: - ✅ RBAC resources are skipped when disabled\n187: - ✅ Existing ServiceAccounts are used when configured\n188: - ✅ Custom RBAC rules are applied correctly\n189: - ✅ Labels and annotations are applied correctly\n190: - ✅ Naming conventions are followed\n191: - ✅ Role/ClusterRole bindings reference correct ServiceAccounts\n192: - ✅ Namespace configuration works correctly\n193: - ✅ Component disable works correctly\n194: \n195: ### Integration Tests\n196: \n197: ```bash\n198: # Permission verification\n199: ./tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n200: ./tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh agentcube\n201: ./tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n202: \n203: # End-to-end tests\n204: ./tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n205: ./tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### Security Tests\n209: \n210: ```bash\n211: ./tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh agentcube\n212: ./tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh agentcube\n213: ./tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh agentcube\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ## Security Features\n217: \n218: ### Principle of Least Privilege\n219: - Router has minimal permissions (secrets only)\n220: - Controller Manager has no default permissions\n221: - Workload Manager requires cluster-wide access but is bounded to specific resources\n222: \n223: ### No Wildcard Permissions\n224: - All permissions use explicit verbs (no `*`)\n225: - Tests verify no wildcard permissions exist\n226: \n227: ### ServiceAccount Security\n228: - Each component uses dedicated ServiceAccount\n229: - Names follow consistent naming convention\n230: - Token automount can be controlled via pod spec\n231: \n232: ### Namespace Isolation\n233: - All namespace-scoped resources use correct namespace\n234: - Role bindings only authorize access within same namespace\n235: - Only workload-manager uses cluster-wide resources\n236: \n237: ## Compliance with Design Document\n238: \n239: The implementation fully complies with the design document:\n240: \n241: ✅ **ServiceAccount Templates**\n242: - Controller-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n243: - Workload-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n244: - Router SA with correct labels and annotations\n245: \n246: ✅ **Role Templates**\n247: - Controller-Manager Role with empty rules by default\n248: - Router Role with secrets-only permissions\n249: - Custom rules support via values.yaml\n250: \n251: ✅ **ClusterRole Template**\n252: - Workload-Manager ClusterRole with all required permissions\n253: - CRD permissions (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n254: - Core resource permissions (pods, services, configmaps, secrets)\n255: - Status and event permissions\n256: \n257: ✅ **RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding Templates**\n258: - Correct bindings between SAs and Roles/ClusterRoles\n259: - Proper namespace references\n260: - Correct roleRef configurations\n261: \n262: ✅ **Helper Templates**\n263: - `agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName`\n264: - `agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName`\n265: - `agentcube.router.serviceAccountName`\n266: \n267: ✅ **Values Configuration**\n268: - Complete RBAC configuration structure\n269: - ClusterRole rules defined\n270: - Component-specific RBAC settings\n271: \n272: ✅ **Tests**\n273: - Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n274: - Integration tests (5 test scripts)\n275: - Security tests (3 test scripts)\n276: - Test documentation\n277: \n278: ## Acceptance Criteria Status\n279: \n280: | Criteria | Status | Notes |\n281: |----------|--------|-------|\n282: | ServiceAccount templates exist and follow naming convention | ✅ | All three components have SA templates |\n283: | Role templates exist with correct permissions | ✅ | Controller-manager and router roles |\n284: | ClusterRole template exists with all required permissions | ✅ | Workload-manager cluster role |\n285: | RoleBinding templates bind SAs to correct Roles | ✅ | All bindings correctly configured |\n286: | ClusterRoleBinding template binds SA to ClusterRole | ✅ | Workload-manager binding |\n287: | Helper templates generate correct SA names | ✅ | Three helper templates defined |\n288: | Values configuration supports all options | ✅ | Complete structure in values.yaml |\n289: | Unit tests cover all RBAC resources | ✅ | 24 test cases |\n290: | Integration tests verify permissions | ✅ | 5 integration test scripts |\n291: | Security tests verify best practices | ✅ | 3 security test scripts |\n292: | Documentation is complete | ✅ | Comprehensive test README |\n293: \n294: ## Future Enhancements\n295: \n296: As outlined in the design document:\n297: \n298: 1. **Pod Security Policy Support** - Add PSP resources for enhanced pod security\n299: 2. **NetworkPolicy RBAC** - Add network policies to restrict inter-component communication\n300: 3. **Dynamic RBAC Management** - Support for dynamic RBAC rule updates\n301: 4. **Audit Logging** - Add audit annotations to RBAC resources\n302: 5. **Multi-Tenant Support** - Namespace-specific RBAC overrides\n303: 6. **RBAC Testing Automation** - Automated permission testing in CI/CD\n304: 7. **ServiceAccount Token Rotation** - Support for token rotation policies\n305: 8. **External RBAC Integration** - OIDC-based service account authentication\n306: \n307: ## References\n308: \n309: - [Design Document](../design.md)\n310: - [Helm Chart Documentation](./README.md)\n311: - [Test Documentation](./tests/README.md)\n312: - [Kubernetes RBAC Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/)\n313: \n314: ## Conclusion\n315: \n316: AR-031 RBAC configuration is fully implemented and tested. All templates, configuration, and tests are in place and follow the design specification. The implementation provides:\n317: \n318: - ✅ Complete RBAC configuration for all three components\n319: - ✅ Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n320: - ✅ Integration tests for permission verification\n321: - ✅ Security tests for best practices\n322: - ✅ Complete documentation\n323: \n324: The RBAC configuration is production-ready and follows Kubernetes security best practices.\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`\n**Language:** YAML (Helm templates)\n**Status:** ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n\n#### Templates (Existing)\nAll RBAC templates were already implemented and follow the design specification:\n\n1. **ServiceAccount Templates**\n   - `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n   - `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775882625629,"end":1775882625639}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882625645,"sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","part":{"id":"prt_d7ada5f00001iPlqIDoBuUs2sG","messageID":"msg_d7ada40c6001571OOtEwIx4y6O","sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9eff929ec4e44d4cb5295b26b52080f0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: AR-031 defines the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components (controller-manager, workload-manager, router). The RBAC configuration ensures proper permission boundaries for each component while maintaining flexibility for custom deployments.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `manifests`  \n8: **Language:** YAML (Helm templates)  \n9: **Source Root:** `/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/`\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### RBAC Hierarchy\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                        AgentCube Namespace                       │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │                                                                  │\n20: │  Controller-Manager          Workload-Manager         Router     │\n21: │  ┌──────────────┐           ┌──────────────┐       ┌───────────┐ │\n22: │  │ ServiceAcc   │           │ ServiceAcc   │       │ Service   │ │\n23: │  │ - name       │           │ - name       │       │ Account   │ │\n24: │  │ - annotations│           │ - annotations│       │           │ │\n25: │  └──────┬───────┘           └──────┬───────┘       └─────┬─────┘ │\n26: │         │                          │                     │       │\n27: │         │ RoleBinding              │ ClusterRoleBinding │ Role    │\n28: │         │ → Role                   │ → ClusterRole      │ Binding │\n29: │         │                          │ (cluster-wide)     │ → Role  │\n30: │         └──────────────┬───────────┘                    └─────┬───┘ │\n31: │                        │                                      │     │\n32: │                        │              Custom Rules           │     │\n33: │                        │         (via values.yaml)           │     │\n34: │                        └──────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n35: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n36: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n37: │                    Cluster-Wide Resources                        │\n38: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n39: │  ClusterRole (workload-manager)                                  │\n40: │  - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh resources (get/list/watch/...)  │\n41: │  - pods, services, configmaps, secrets (get/list/watch/...)     │\n42: │  - pods/status (get)                                             │\n43: │  - events (create/patch)                                         │\n44: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### Components\n48: \n49: | Component | Location | Responsibility |\n50: |-----------|----------|----------------|\n51: | ServiceAccount Templates | `templates/*/serviceaccount.yaml` | Identity for each component pod |\n52: | Role Templates | `templates/*/rbac.yaml` | Namespace-scoped permissions |\n53: | ClusterRole Template | `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` | Cluster-scoped permissions |\n54: | RoleBinding Templates | `templates/*/rbac.yaml` | Bind SAs to namespace Roles |\n55: | ClusterRoleBinding Template | `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` | Bind SA to cluster-wide Role |\n56: | Helper Templates | `templates/_helpers.tpl` | Name generation logic |\n57: \n58: ### Permission Scope\n59: \n60: | Component | Resource Scope | Required APIs |\n61: |-----------|----------------|---------------|\n62: | controller-manager | Namespace (empty by default) | Custom rules via `values.controllerManager.rbac.rules` |\n63: | workload-manager | Cluster | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n64: | router | Namespace | Secrets only |\n65: \n66: ## Detailed Implementation\n67: \n68: ### 1. ServiceAccount Templates\n69: \n70: #### Controller-Manager ServiceAccount\n71: \n72: **Location:** `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n73: \n74: ```yaml\n75: {{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n76: apiVersion: v1\n77: kind: ServiceAccount\n78: metadata:\n79:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n80:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n81:   labels:\n82:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n83:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n84:   {{- with .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n85:   annotations:\n86:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n87:   {{- end }}\n88: {{- end }}\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Configuration:**\n92: - Enabled when `controllerManager.enabled` and `controllerManager.serviceAccount.create` are true\n93: - Name: Full chart name (default) or `controllerManager.serviceAccount.name` override\n94: - Labels: Standard chart labels + component label\n95: - Annotations: From `controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations`\n96: \n97: #### Workload-Manager ServiceAccount\n98: \n99: **Location:** `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n100: \n101: ```yaml\n102: {{- if and .Values.workloadManager.enabled .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n103: apiVersion: v1\n104: kind: ServiceAccount\n105: metadata:\n106:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n107:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n108:   labels:\n109:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n110:     app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n111:   {{- with .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n112:   annotations:\n113:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n114:   {{- end }}\n115: {{- end }}\n116: ```\n117: \n118: **Configuration:**\n119: - Name: `{fullname}-workload-manager` (default) or override\n120: - Requires cluster-wide permissions via ClusterRoleBinding\n121: \n122: #### Router ServiceAccount\n123: \n124: **Location:** `templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml`\n125: \n126: ```yaml\n127: {{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\n128: apiVersion: v1\n129: kind: ServiceAccount\n130: metadata:\n131:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n132:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n133:   labels:\n134:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n135:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n136:   {{- with .Values.router.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n137:   annotations:\n138:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n139:   {{- end }}\n140: {{- end }}\n141: ```\n142: \n143: **Configuration:**\n144: - Name: `{fullname}-router` (default) or override\n145: - Minimal permissions: only secrets access\n146: \n147: ### 2. Role Templates\n148: \n149: #### Controller-Manager Role\n150: \n151: **Location:** `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml`\n152: \n153: ```yaml\n154: {{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.rbac.create }}\n155: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n156: kind: Role\n157: metadata:\n158:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n159:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n160:   labels:\n161:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n162:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n163: rules:\n164: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules }}\n165: {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules | nindent 2 }}\n166: {{- else }}\n167:   []\n168: {{- end }}\n169: ---\n170: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n171: kind: RoleBinding\n172: metadata:\n173:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n174:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n175:   labels:\n176:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n177:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n178: roleRef:\n179:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n180:   kind: Role\n181:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n182: subjects:\n183: - kind: ServiceAccount\n184:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n185:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n186: {{- end }}\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Features:**\n190: - Empty rules by default (controller-manager may not need namespace-scoped permissions)\n191: - Custom rules via `controllerManager.rbac.rules`\n192: - RoleBinding binds ServiceAccount to Role in same namespace\n193: \n194: #### Router Role\n195: \n196: **Location:** `templates/router/rbac.yaml`\n197: \n198: ```yaml\n199: {{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n200: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n201: kind: Role\n202: metadata:\n203:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n204:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n205:   labels:\n206:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n207:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n208: rules:\n209: - apiGroups:\n210:   - \"\"\n211:   resources:\n212:   - secrets\n213:   verbs:\n214:   - get\n215:   - list\n216:   - watch\n217: ---\n218: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n219: kind: RoleBinding\n220: metadata:\n221:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n222:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n223:   labels:\n224:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n225:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n226: roleRef:\n227:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n228:   kind: Role\n229:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n230: subjects:\n231: - kind: ServiceAccount\n232:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n233:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n234: {{- end }}\n235: ```\n236: \n237: **Features:**\n238: - Read-only access to secrets (get/list/watch)\n239: - Used for reading configuration secrets in router namespace\n240: \n241: ### 3. ClusterRole Template\n242: \n243: #### Workload-Manager ClusterRole\n244: \n245: **Location:** `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml`\n246: \n247: ```yaml\n248: {{- if and .Values.workloadManager.enabled .Values.workloadManager.rbac.create }}\n249: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n250: kind: ClusterRole\n251: metadata:\n252:   name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n253:   labels:\n254:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n255:     app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n256: rules:\n257: {{- toYaml .Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules | nindent 0 }}\n258: ---\n259: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n260: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n261: metadata:\n262:   name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n263:   labels:\n264:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n265:     app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n266: roleRef:\n267:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n268:   kind: ClusterRole\n269:   name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n270: subjects:\n271: - kind: ServiceAccount\n272:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n273:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n274: {{- end }}\n275: ```\n276: \n277: **Rules Configuration (from `values.yaml`):**\n278: \n279: ```yaml\n280: rbac:\n281:   clusterRole:\n282:     rules:\n283:     - apiGroups:\n284:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n285:       resources:\n286:       - agentruntimes\n287:       - codeinterpreters\n288:       verbs:\n289:       - get\n290:       - list\n291:       - watch\n292:       - create\n293:       - update\n294:       - patch\n295:       - delete\n296:     - apiGroups:\n297:       - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n298:       resources:\n299:       - agentruntimes/status\n300:       - codeinterpreters/status\n301:       verbs:\n302:       - get\n303:       - update\n304:       - patch\n305:     - apiGroups:\n306:       - \"\"\n307:       resources:\n308:       - pods\n309:       - services\n310:       - configmaps\n311:       - secrets\n312:       verbs:\n313:       - get\n314:       - list\n315:       - watch\n316:       - create\n317:       - update\n318:       - patch\n319:       - delete\n320:     - apiGroups:\n321:       - \"\"\n322:       resources:\n323:       - pods/status\n324:       verbs:\n325:       - get\n326:     - apiGroups:\n327:       - \"\"\n328:       resources:\n329:       - events\n330:       verbs:\n331:       - create\n332:       - patch\n333: ```\n334: \n335: **Permission Breakdown:**\n336: - CRD resources (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters): Full CRUD + status\n337: - Workload resources (pods, services, configmaps, secrets): Full CRUD\n338: - Pod status: Read-only\n339: - Events: Create and patch (for event recording)\n340: \n341: ### 4. Helper Templates\n342: \n343: #### ServiceAccount Name Helpers\n344: \n345: ```yaml\n346: {{- define \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n347: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n348: {{- default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n349: {{- else }}\n350: {{- default \"default\" .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n351: {{- end }}\n352: {{- end }}\n353: \n354: {{- define \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n355: {{- if .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n356: {{- default (printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n357: {{- else }}\n358: {{- default \"default\" .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n359: {{- end }}\n360: {{- end }}\n361: \n362: {{- define \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n363: {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\n364: {{- default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n365: {{- else }}\n366: {{- default \"default\" .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n367: {{- end }}\n368: {{- end }}\n369: ```\n370: \n371: **Logic:**\n372: - If creating ServiceAccount: use provided name or generate default\n373: - If using existing ServiceAccount: use provided name or \"default\"\n374: \n375: ## Data Structures\n376: \n377: ### Values Configuration\n378: \n379: ```yaml\n380: # ServiceAccount configuration\n381: controllerManager:\n382:   enabled: true\n383:   serviceAccount:\n384:     create: true\n385:     name: \"\"\n386:     annotations:\n387:       example-annotation: value\n388:   rbac:\n389:     create: true\n390:     rules: []\n391: \n392: workloadManager:\n393:   enabled: true\n394:   serviceAccount:\n395:     create: true\n396:     name: \"\"\n397:     annotations: {}\n398:   rbac:\n399:     create: true\n400:     rules: []\n401: \n402: router:\n403:   enabled: true\n404:   serviceAccount:\n405:     create: true\n406:     name: \"\"\n407:     annotations: {}\n408:   rbac:\n409:     create: true\n410:     rules: []\n411: \n412: # Global RBAC configuration\n413: rbac:\n414:   create: true\n415:   clusterRole:\n416:     create: true\n417:     rules:\n418:     # CRD permissions\n419:     - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n420:       resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n421:       verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n422:     # CRD status permissions\n423:     - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n424:       resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n425:       verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n426:     # Core resources\n427:     - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n428:       resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n429:       verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n430:     # Pod status\n431:     - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n432:       resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n433:       verbs: [\"get\"]\n434:     # Events\n435:     - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n436:       resources: [\"events\"]\n437:       verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ### Kubernetes Resource Specifications\n441: \n442: #### ServiceAccount\n443: \n444: ```yaml\n445: apiVersion: v1\n446: kind: ServiceAccount\n447: metadata:\n448:   name: string\n449:   namespace: string\n450:   labels:\n451:     helm.sh/chart: string\n452:     app.kubernetes.io/name: string\n453:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: string\n454:     app.kubernetes.io/version: string\n455:     app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: string\n456:     app.kubernetes.io/component: string\n457:   annotations:\n458:     # Custom annotations from values\n459: ```\n460: \n461: #### Role\n462: \n463: ```yaml\n464: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n465: kind: Role\n466: metadata:\n467:   name: string\n468:   namespace: string\n469:   labels: {}\n470: rules:\n471: - apiGroups: [\"\"]  # Core API group is \"\"\n472:   resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n473:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n474: ```\n475: \n476: #### ClusterRole\n477: \n478: ```yaml\n479: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n480: kind: ClusterRole\n481: metadata:\n482:   name: string\n483:   labels: {}\n484: rules:\n485: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n486:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n487:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n488: ```\n489: \n490: #### RoleBinding\n491: \n492: ```yaml\n493: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n494: kind: RoleBinding\n495: metadata:\n496:   name: string\n497:   namespace: string\n498:   labels: {}\n499: roleRef:\n500:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n501:   kind: Role\n502:   name: string\n503: subjects:\n504: - kind: ServiceAccount\n505:   name: string\n506:   namespace: string\n507: ```\n508: \n509: #### ClusterRoleBinding\n510: \n511: ```yaml\n512: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n513: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n514: metadata:\n515:   name: string\n516:   labels: {}\n517: roleRef:\n518:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n519:   kind: ClusterRole\n520:   name: string\n521: subjects:\n522: - kind: ServiceAccount\n523:   name: string\n524:   namespace: string\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ## API Contracts\n528: \n529: ### Kubernetes RBAC API\n530: \n531: #### API Groups and Resources\n532: \n533: | API Group | Version | Resources | Verbs |\n534: |-----------|---------|-----------|-------|\n535: | `rbac.authorization.k8s.io` | v1 | roles, rolebindings, clusterroles, clusterrolebindings | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n536: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | agentruntimes, codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n537: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | agentruntimes/status, codeinterpreters/status | get, update, patch |\n538: | `` (core) | v1 | pods, services, configmaps, secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n539: | `` (core) | v1 | pods/status | get |\n540: | `` (core) | v1 | events | create, patch |\n541: \n542: #### ServiceAccount Authentication\n543: \n544: Pods using a ServiceAccount automatically receive:\n545: - Mounted token at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n546: - Mounted CA certificate at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/ca.crt`\n547: - API server reference at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/namespace`\n548: \n549: The Workload Manager uses this token to authenticate to the Kubernetes API.\n550: \n551: ### Helm Template API\n552: \n553: #### Template Variables\n554: \n555: | Variable | Type | Description |\n556: |----------|------|-------------|\n557: | `.Values.component.enabled` | bool | Component enable flag |\n558: | `.Values.component.serviceAccount.create` | bool | Create SA or use existing |\n559: | `.Values.component.serviceAccount.name` | string | SA name override |\n560: | `.Values.component.serviceAccount.annotations` | dict | SA annotations |\n561: | `.Values.component.rbac.create` | bool | Create RBAC resources |\n562: | `.Values.component.rbac.rules` | list | Custom Role rules |\n563: | `.Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules` | list | ClusterRole rules |\n564: | `.Values.global.namespaceOverride` | string | Namespace override |\n565: | `.Chart.Name` | string | Chart name |\n566: | `.Chart.Version` | string | Chart version |\n567: | `.Release.Name` | string | Release name |\n568: | `.Release.Namespace` | string | Release namespace |\n569: \n570: #### Template Functions\n571: \n572: ```yaml\n573: # Standard chart name\n574: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n575: \n576: # Component-specific SA names\n577: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n578: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n579: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n580: \n581: # Namespace resolution\n582: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n583: \n584: # Standard labels\n585: {{ include \"agentcube.labels\" . }}\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ## Error Handling\n589: \n590: ### Validation Errors\n591: \n592: #### Missing Configuration\n593: \n594: **Scenario:** Component enabled but RBAC disabled\n595: \n596: **Validation:** \n597: ```yaml\n598: {{- if and .Values.component.enabled (not .Values.component.rbac.create) }}\n599: {{- fail \"Component enabled but RBAC creation disabled\" }}\n600: {{- end }}\n601: ```\n602: \n603: **User Message:**\n604: ```\n605: Error: component enabled but RBAC creation disabled\n606: Please set component.rbac.create to true or disable the component\n607: ```\n608: \n609: #### Invalid ServiceAccount Name\n610: \n611: **Scenario:** ServiceAccount name exceeds 253 characters\n612: \n613: **Prevention:** Helm truncates names to 63 characters via `| trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\"`\n614: \n615: #### Invalid RBAC Rules\n616: \n617: **Scenario:** Invalid verbs or API groups in custom rules\n618: \n619: **Prevention:** Kubernetes API server validates rules at resource creation\n620: \n621: **Error Response:**\n622: ```\n623: Error: failed to create rolebinding: Role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io \"name\" is invalid: rules[0].verbs[0]: Unsupported value: \"invalidverb\"\n624: ```\n625: \n626: ### Deployment Errors\n627: \n628: #### ServiceAccount Not Found\n629: \n630: **Scenario:** Using existing ServiceAccount that doesn't exist\n631: \n632: **Error:** Pod fails to start with admission error\n633: \n634: **User Action:** Create the ServiceAccount or set `serviceAccount.create: true`\n635: \n636: ```\n637: Warning  FailedCreate  5m  replicaset  Error creating: pods \"xyz\" is forbidden:\n638: error looking up service account component/xyz: serviceaccount \"xyz\" not found\n639: ```\n640: \n641: #### Permission Denied\n642: \n643: **Scenario:** Component lacks required permissions\n644: \n645: **Error:** Application logs show 403 Forbidden from Kubernetes API\n646: \n647: **Example:**\n648: ```\n649: E0411 12:00:00.000000       1 runtime.go:78] Failed to list pods:\n650: pods is forbidden: User \"system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workload-manager\"\n651: cannot list resource \"pods\" in API group \"\" at the cluster scope\n652: ```\n653: \n654: **Troubleshooting:**\n655: 1. Verify ServiceAccount is bound to correct Role/ClusterRole\n656: 2. Verify Role/ClusterRole has required rules\n657: 3. Verify ClusterRoleBinding references correct namespace\n658: \n659: #### RBAC Policy Too Permissive\n660: \n661: **Scenario:** Custom rules grant excessive permissions\n662: \n663: **Prevention:** Document required permissions in `values.yaml` comments\n664: \n665: **Recommendation:** Use specific verbs instead of wildcard `*`\n666: \n667: ## Testing Strategy\n668: \n669: ### Unit Tests\n670: \n671: #### Template Rendering Tests\n672: \n673: **Test File:** `manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/rbac_test.yaml`\n674: \n675: ```yaml\n676: suite: Test RBAC Configuration\n677: templates:\n678:   - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n679:   - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n680:   - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n681:   - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n682:   - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n683:   - templates/router/rbac.yaml\n684: tests:\n685:   - it: Creates all RBAC resources when enabled\n686:     set:\n687:       controllerManager.enabled: true\n688:       workloadManager.enabled: true\n689:       router.enabled: true\n690:       controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n691:       workloadManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n692:       router.serviceAccount.create: true\n693:       controllerManager.rbac.create: true\n694:       workloadManager.rbac.create: true\n695:       router.rbac.create: true\n696:     asserts:\n697:       - isKind:\n698:           of: ServiceAccount\n699:       - isKind:\n700:           of: Role\n701:       - isKind:\n702:           of: RoleBinding\n703:       - isKind:\n704:           of: ClusterRole\n705:       - isKind:\n706:           of: ClusterRoleBinding\n707: \n708:   - it: Skips RBAC creation when disabled\n709:     set:\n710:       controllerManager.rbac.create: false\n711:     asserts:\n712:       - hasDocuments:\n713:           count: 0\n714: \n715:   - it: Uses existing ServiceAccount when create is false\n716:     set:\n717:       controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: false\n718:       controllerManager.serviceAccount.name: existing-sa\n719:     asserts:\n720:       - hasDocuments:\n721:           count: 0\n722: \n723:   - it: Applies custom RBAC rules for controller-manager\n724:     set:\n725:       controllerManager.rbac.rules:\n726:         - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n727:           resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n728:           verbs: [\"get\"]\n729:     asserts:\n730:       - equal:\n731:           path: rules[0].resources\n732:           value: [\"configmaps\"]\n733:       - equal:\n734:           path: rules[0].verbs\n735:           value: [\"get\"]\n736: \n737:   - it: Router Role has only secrets permission\n738:     asserts:\n739:       - equal:\n740:           path: rules[0].resources\n741:           value: [\"secrets\"]\n742:       - equal:\n743:           path: rules[0].verbs\n744:           value: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n745: \n746:   - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD permissions\n747:     asserts:\n748:       - contains:\n749:           path: rules\n750:           content:\n751:             apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n752:             resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n753: ```\n754: \n755: ### Integration Tests\n756: \n757: #### Permission Verification\n758: \n759: **Test 1: Verify Workload Manager Can Create Pods**\n760: \n761: ```bash\n762: #!/bin/bash\n763: # Test: Workload Manager can create pods\n764: kubectl auth can-i create pods \\\n765:   --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-workload-manager \\\n766:   -n agentcube\n767: # Expected: yes\n768: ```\n769: \n770: **Test 2: Verify Router Can List Secrets**\n771: \n772: ```bash\n773: #!/bin/bash\n774: # Test: Router can list secrets\n775: kubectl auth can-i list secrets \\\n776:   --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router \\\n777:   -n agentcube\n778: # Expected: yes\n779: ```\n780: \n781: **Test 3: Verify Controller Manager Cannot Delete Pods**\n782: \n783: ```bash\n784: #!/bin/bash\n785: # Test: Controller manager cannot delete pods (by default)\n786: kubectl auth can-i delete pods \\\n787:   --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube \\\n788:   -n agentcube\n789: # Expected: no (if no custom rules)\n790: ```\n791: \n792: #### End-to-End Tests\n793: \n794: **Test 1: Deploy AgentCube with Custom RBAC**\n795: \n796: ```yaml\n797: # test-values.yaml\n798: controllerManager:\n799:   rbac:\n800:     rules:\n801:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n802:         resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n803:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ```bash\n807: #!/bin/bash\n808: # Test deployment with custom RBAC\n809: helm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n810:   -f test-values.yaml \\\n811:   --namespace agentcube \\\n812:   --create-namespace\n813: \n814: # Verify Role has custom rules\n815: kubectl get role agentcube -n agentcube -o yaml | grep -A 5 \"resources:\"\n816: \n817: # Clean up\n818: helm uninstall agentcube -n agentcube\n819: ```\n820: \n821: **Test 2: Deploy with Existing ServiceAccount**\n822: \n823: ```bash\n824: #!/bin/bash\n825: # Test: Use existing ServiceAccount\n826: kubectl create serviceaccount existing-router -n agentcube\n827: \n828: helm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n829:   --set router.serviceAccount.create=false \\\n830:   --set router.serviceAccount.name=existing-router \\\n831:   --namespace agentcube\n832: \n833: # Verify Router uses existing SA\n834: kubectl get deployment agentcube-router -n agentcube \\\n835:   -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName}'\n836: \n837: # Expected: existing-router\n838: ```\n839: \n840: ### Security Tests\n841: \n842: **Test 1: Principle of Least Privilege**\n843: \n844: ```bash\n845: #!/bin/bash\n846: # Test: Verify minimal permissions\n847: components=(\"controller-manager\" \"workload-manager\" \"router\")\n848: \n849: for component in \"${components[@]}\"; do\n850:   sa_name=\"agentcube-${component//manager/manager}\"\n851:   echo \"Testing $component permissions...\"\n852:   \n853:   # Get all permissions\n854:   kubectl auth can-i \"*\" \"*\" \\\n855:     --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:$sa_name \\\n856:     --all-namespaces \\\n857:     2>&1 | grep -i \"no\"\n858: done\n859: ```\n860: \n861: **Test 2: No Wildcard Permissions**\n862: \n863: ```bash\n864: #!/bin/bash\n865: # Test: Verify no wildcard (*) verbs\n866: for role in $(kubectl get roles -n agentcube -o name); do\n867:   echo \"Checking $role for wildcard verbs...\"\n868:   kubectl get $role -n agentcube -o yaml | grep -i \"verbs:\\s*-\\s*[*]\"\n869:   if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\n870:     echo \"WARNING: Wildcard verb found in $role\"\n871:   fi\n872: done\n873: ```\n874: \n875: **Test 3: ServiceAccount Token Automount**\n876: \n877: ```bash\n878: #!/bin/bash\n879: # Test: Verify token automount is controlled\n880: for deployment in $(kubectl get deployments -n agentcube -o name); do\n881:   echo \"Checking $deployment...\"\n882:   kubectl get $deployment -n agentcube -o yaml \\\n883:     | grep -A 5 \"automountServiceAccountToken\"\n884: done\n885: ```\n886: \n887: ### Performance Tests\n888: \n889: **Test 1: RBAC Evaluation Performance**\n890: \n891: ```bash\n892: #!/bin/bash\n893: # Test: Measure RBAC evaluation time\n894: time kubectl auth can-i get pods \\\n895:   --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-workload-manager \\\n896:   -n agentcube\n897: ```\n898: \n899: **Test 2: Large Scale RBAC**\n900: \n901: ```yaml\n902: # stress-test-values.yaml\n903: controllerManager:\n904:   rbac:\n905:     rules:\n906:       # Add 100 custom rules\n907:       {{- range $i := until 100 }}\n908:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n909:         resources: [\"resource-{{ $i }}\"]\n910:         verbs: [\"get\"]\n911:       {{- end }}\n912: ```\n913: \n914: ```bash\n915: #!/bin/bash\n916: # Test: Large scale RBAC configuration\n917: helm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n918:   -f stress-test-values.yaml \\\n919:   --namespace agentcube\n920: \n921: # Measure template render time\n922: time helm template agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n923:   -f stress-test-values.yaml\n924: ```\n925: \n926: ## Security Considerations\n927: \n928: ### 1. Principle of Least Privilege\n929: \n930: - Default RBAC rules provide only necessary permissions\n931: - Router has minimal permissions (secrets only)\n932: - Workload Manager requires cluster-wide access but is bounded to specific resources\n933: - Controller Manager has no default namespace-scoped permissions\n934: \n935: ### 2. ServiceAccount Security\n936: \n937: - Each component uses dedicated ServiceAccount\n938: - ServiceAccount names follow naming convention\n939: - Automount of ServiceAccount token can be controlled via `automountServiceAccountToken` in pod spec\n940: - Tokens are mounted at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/`\n941: \n942: ### 3. RBAC Scope Management\n943: \n944: - Namespace-scoped: Role, RoleBinding, ServiceAccount\n945: - Cluster-scoped: ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding\n946: - Workload Manager is the only component requiring cluster-wide access\n947: - Router and Controller Manager use namespace-scoped permissions\n948: \n949: ### 4. Custom Rule Validation\n950: \n951: When adding custom RBAC rules via `values.yaml`, ensure:\n952: - Avoid wildcard `*` verbs unless necessary\n953: - Specify exact API groups and resources\n954: - Use most restrictive verbs (e.g., `get` instead of `*`)\n955: - Document the reason for each permission\n956: \n957: ### 5. Namespace Isolation\n958: \n959: - All RBAC resources are namespaced except ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding\n960: - ServiceAccount namespaced to `agentcube` namespace by default\n961: - Role bindings only authorize access within the same namespace\n962: \n963: ## Future Enhancements\n964: \n965: 1. **Pod Security Policy Support**\n966:    - Add PSP resources for enhanced pod security\n967:    - Support for Kubernetes 1.25+ Pod Security Standards\n968: \n969: 2. **NetworkPolicy RBAC**\n970:    - Add network policies to restrict inter-component communication\n971:    - Configure network policies based on RBAC permissions\n972: \n973: 3. **Dynamic RBAC Management**\n974:    - Support for dynamic RBAC rule updates without reinstall\n975:    - RBAC rules as ConfigMaps for easier management\n976: \n977: 4. **Audit Logging**\n978:    - Add audit annotations to RBAC resources\n979:    - Track permission changes over time\n980: \n981: 5. **Multi-Tenant Support**\n982:    - Support for multi-tenant RBAC configurations\n983:    - Namespace-specific RBAC overrides\n984: \n985: 6. **RBAC Testing Automation**\n986:    - Automated permission testing in CI/CD\n987:    - Permission drift detection\n988: \n989: 7. **ServiceAccount Token Rotation**\n990:    - Support for token rotation policies\n991:    - Configurable token expiration\n992: \n993: 8. **External RBAC Integration**\n994:    - Support for external authentication providers\n995:    - OIDC-based service account authentication\n\n(End of file - total 995 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-031 defines the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components (controller-manager, workload-manager, router). The RBAC configuration ensures proper permission boundaries for each component while maintaining flexibility for custom deployments.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML (Helm templates)  \n**Source Root:** `/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### RBAC Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        AgentCube Namespace                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  Controller-Manager          Workload-Manager         Router     │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775882625627,"end":1775882625642}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882625659,"sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","part":{"id":"prt_d7ada5cbf001y1uOeUYUh6wn9E","messageID":"msg_d7ada40c6001571OOtEwIx4y6O","sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-28fc2e67c96946009e876341e6e1e16c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: manifests\n4: \n5: ### ServiceAccount\n6: \n7: #### ServiceAccount Definition\n8: \n9: ```yaml\n10: apiVersion: v1\n11: kind: ServiceAccount\n12: metadata:\n13:   name: <service-account-name>\n14:   namespace: <namespace>\n15: ```\n16: \n17: **Parameters:**\n18: - `name`: ServiceAccount name\n19: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n20: \n21: ### Role\n22: \n23: #### Role Definition\n24: \n25: ```yaml\n26: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n27: kind: Role\n28: metadata:\n29:   name: <role-name>\n30:   namespace: <namespace>\n31: rules:\n32:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n33:     resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n34:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n35: ```\n36: \n37: **Parameters:**\n38: - `name`: Role name\n39: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n40: - `rules`: List of policy rules\n41: \n42: ### RoleBinding\n43: \n44: #### RoleBinding Definition\n45: \n46: ```yaml\n47: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n48: kind: RoleBinding\n49: metadata:\n50:   name: <role-binding-name>\n51:   namespace: <namespace>\n52: subjects:\n53:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n54:     name: <service-account-name>\n55:     namespace: <namespace>\n56: roleRef:\n57:   kind: Role\n58:   name: <role-name>\n59:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Parameters:**\n63: - `name`: RoleBinding name\n64: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n65: - `subjects`: List of subjects (ServiceAccounts, Users, Groups)\n66: - `roleRef`: Reference to the Role\n67: \n68: ### ClusterRole (Optional)\n69: \n70: #### ClusterRole Definition\n71: \n72: ```yaml\n73: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n74: kind: ClusterRole\n75: metadata:\n76:   name: <cluster-role-name>\n77: rules:\n78:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n79:     resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\"]\n80:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n81: ```\n82: \n83: **Parameters:**\n84: - `name`: ClusterRole name\n85: - `rules`: List of policy rules\n86: \n87: ### ClusterRoleBinding (Optional)\n88: \n89: #### ClusterRoleBinding Definition\n90: \n91: ```yaml\n92: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n93: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n94: metadata:\n95:   name: <cluster-role-binding-name>\n96: subjects:\n97:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n98:     name: <service-account-name>\n99:     namespace: <namespace>\n100: roleRef:\n101:   kind: ClusterRole\n102:   name: <cluster-role-name>\n103:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n104: ```\n105: \n106: **Parameters:**\n107: - `name`: ClusterRoleBinding name\n108: - `subjects`: List of subjects\n109: - `roleRef`: Reference to the ClusterRole\n110: \n111: ## Common API Resources\n112: \n113: ### Core API (apiGroups: [\"\"])\n114: \n115: Common resources:\n116: - `pods`\n117: - `services`\n118: - `configmaps`\n119: - `secrets`\n120: - `persistentvolumeclaims`\n121: - `events`\n122: \n123: ### Apps API (apiGroups: [\"apps\"])\n124: \n125: Common resources:\n126: - `deployments`\n127: - `statefulsets`\n128: - `daemonsets`\n129: - `replicasets`\n130: \n131: ## Common Verbs\n132: \n133: - `get`, `list`, `watch` - Read operations\n134: - `create` - Create resources\n135: - `update`, `patch` - Update resources\n136: - `delete` - Delete resources\n137: - `*` - All operations\n138: \n139: ## Best Practices\n140: \n141: - Principle of least privilege\n142: - Namespace-scoped permissions where possible\n143: - Use specific resource names with `resourceNames` field for fine-grained control\n144: - Regular review of RBAC policies\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Specification\n\n## Module: manifests\n\n### ServiceAccount\n\n#### ServiceAccount Definition\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: <service-account-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `name`: ServiceAccount name\n- `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md","time":{"start":1775882625625,"end":1775882625656}}}}
