{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882635546,"sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","part":{"id":"prt_d7ada88cc001TLWsvsGm794cTq","messageID":"msg_d7ada62ae001KZkGFXF2HuuR7D","sessionID":"ses_285262256ffeVOpYy41XYQmqYV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a1cd32b0e52441ae879b8cdcf4f2dd99","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # RBAC Tests for AgentCube Helm Chart\n2: \n3: This directory contains comprehensive tests for the RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration of the AgentCube Helm chart.\n4: \n5: ## Test Structure\n6: \n7: ```\n8: tests/\n9: ├── rbac_test.yaml                          # Helm unit tests for RBAC templates\n10: ├── controller-manager_test.yaml           # Controller manager tests\n11: ├── router_test.yaml                        # Router tests\n12: ├── workload-manager_test.yaml             # Workload manager tests\n13: └── integration/                            # Integration and security tests\n14:     ├── test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n15:     ├── test_router_permissions.sh\n16:     ├── test_controller_manager_permissions.sh\n17:     ├── test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n18:     ├── test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n19:     ├── test_least_privilege.sh\n20:     ├── test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\n21:     └── test_token_automount.sh\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ## Prerequisites\n25: \n26: - **Helm** (v3.x)\n27: - **kubectl** configured with cluster access\n28: - **Helm unittest plugin** for unit tests\n29: - Access to a Kubernetes cluster (for integration tests)\n30: \n31: ### Installing Helm unittest plugin\n32: \n33: ```bash\n34: helm plugin install https://github.com/quintush/helm-unittest\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ## Running Tests\n38: \n39: ### Unit Tests (Helm Template Tests)\n40: \n41: Run all unit tests:\n42: \n43: ```bash\n44: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n45: ```\n46: \n47: Run specific test file:\n48: \n49: ```bash\n50: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -f tests/rbac_test.yaml\n51: ```\n52: \n53: Run tests with verbose output:\n54: \n55: ```bash\n56: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -v\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Integration Tests\n60: \n61: Integration tests require a deployed AgentCube instance. Run them from the project root:\n62: \n63: ```bash\n64: # Test workload manager permissions\n65: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh [namespace]\n66: \n67: # Test router permissions\n68: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh [namespace]\n69: \n70: # Test controller manager permissions (should NOT have delete permissions)\n71: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh [namespace]\n72: \n73: # Deploy with custom RBAC\n74: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n75: \n76: # Deploy with existing ServiceAccount\n77: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Security Tests\n81: \n82: Run security tests to verify RBAC best practices:\n83: \n84: ```bash\n85: # Test principle of least privilege\n86: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh [namespace]\n87: \n88: # Test for no wildcard permissions\n89: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh [namespace]\n90: \n91: # Test ServiceAccount token automount configuration\n92: ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh [namespace]\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Run All Tests\n96: \n97: ```bash\n98: # Unit tests\n99: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n100: \n101: # Integration tests (requires deployed instance)\n102: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n103: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh\n104: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh\n105: \n106: # Security tests\n107: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh\n108: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\n109: NAMESPACE=agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Test Coverage\n113: \n114: ### Unit Tests (rbac_test.yaml)\n115: \n116: The unit tests verify:\n117: \n118: - ✅ All RBAC resources are created when enabled\n119: - ✅ RBAC resources are skipped when disabled\n120: - ✅ Existing ServiceAccounts are used when configured\n121: - ✅ Custom RBAC rules are applied for controller-manager\n122: - ✅ Controller-manager Role has empty rules by default\n123: - ✅ Router Role has only secrets permission\n124: - ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD permissions\n125: - ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD status permissions\n126: - ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has core resource permissions\n127: - ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has pod status permissions\n128: - ✅ Workload Manager ClusterRole has event permissions\n129: - ✅ ServiceAccounts have correct labels\n130: - ✅ Roles and ClusterRoles have correct labels\n131: - ✅ ServiceAccount names follow naming convention\n132: - ✅ RoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n133: - ✅ ClusterRoleBinding references correct ServiceAccount\n134: - ✅ ServiceAccount annotations are applied\n135: - ✅ Custom ServiceAccount name is used when specified\n136: - ✅ Resources are skipped when components are disabled\n137: - ✅ RoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n138: - ✅ ClusterRoleBinding subjects reference correct namespace\n139: - ✅ All RBAC resources use correct namespace\n140: - ✅ Custom namespace is used when specified\n141: - ✅ fullnameOverride is used in resource names\n142: \n143: ### Integration Tests\n144: \n145: Permission Verification Tests:\n146: \n147: 1. **test_workload_manager_permissions.sh**\n148:    - Verifies workload-manager can create pods\n149:    - Expected: yes\n150: \n151: 2. **test_router_permissions.sh**\n152:    - Verifies router can list secrets\n153:    - Expected: yes\n154: \n155: 3. **test_controller_manager_permissions.sh**\n156:    - Verifies controller-manager cannot delete pods (by default)\n157:    - Expected: no (if no custom rules)\n158: \n159: End-to-End Tests:\n160: \n161: 4. **test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh**\n162:    - Deploys AgentCube with custom RBAC rules\n163:    - Verifies Role has custom configmaps rules\n164:    - Cleans up test deployment\n165: \n166: 5. **test_existing_serviceaccount.sh**\n167:    - Creates an existing ServiceAccount\n168:    - Deploys chart using existing SA\n169:    - Verifies Router uses existing SA\n170:    - Cleans up test deployment\n171: \n172: ### Security Tests\n173: \n174: 1. **test_least_privilege.sh**\n175:    - Verifies each component cannot perform all operations\n176:    - Ensures principle of least privilege is followed\n177: \n178: 2. **test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh**\n179:    - Checks for wildcard (*) verbs in all Roles\n180:    - Checks for wildcard (*) verbs in all ClusterRoles\n181:    - Flags any wildcard permissions for review\n182: \n183: 3. **test_token_automount.sh**\n184:    - Checks automountServiceAccountToken setting on all deployments\n185:    - Reports current state for security review\n186: \n187: ## RBAC Architecture\n188: \n189: ### Components\n190: \n191: | Component | Resource Scope | ServiceAccount | Role/ClusterRole | Permissions |\n192: |-----------|---------------|----------------|------------------|-------------|\n193: | controller-manager | Namespace | `agentcube` | Role | Custom rules (empty by default) |\n194: | workload-manager | Cluster | `agentcube-workload-manager` | ClusterRole | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n195: | router | Namespace | `agentcube-router` | Role | Secrets (get, list, watch) |\n196: \n197: ### ClusterRole Rules (workload-manager)\n198: \n199: The workload-manager ClusterRole includes:\n200: \n201: 1. **CRD resources** (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n202:    - agentruntimes, codeinterpreters: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n203:    - agentruntimes/status, codeinterpreters/status: get, update, patch\n204: \n205: 2. **Core resources** (\"\")\n206:    - pods, services, configmaps, secrets: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete\n207:    - pods/status: get\n208:    - events: create, patch\n209: \n210: ### Role Rules (router)\n211: \n212: The router Role includes:\n213: \n214: - secrets: get, list, watch\n215: \n216: ### Role Rules (controller-manager)\n217: \n218: The controller-manager Role includes:\n219: \n220: - Custom rules via `controllerManager.rbac.rules` (empty by default)\n221: \n222: ## Configuration\n223: \n224: ### Enable/Disable RBAC\n225: \n226: ```yaml\n227: controllerManager:\n228:   rbac:\n229:     create: true  # Set to false to disable\n230: \n231: workloadManager:\n232:   rbac:\n233:     create: true\n234: \n235: router:\n236:   rbac:\n237:     create: true\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### Use Existing ServiceAccount\n241: \n242: ```yaml\n243: controllerManager:\n244:   serviceAccount:\n245:     create: false\n246:     name: existing-sa\n247: \n248: workloadManager:\n249:   serviceAccount:\n250:     create: false\n251:     name: existing-wm-sa\n252: \n253: router:\n254:   serviceAccount:\n255:     create: false\n256:     name: existing-router-sa\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ### Custom RBAC Rules\n260: \n261: ```yaml\n262: controllerManager:\n263:   rbac:\n264:     rules:\n265:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n266:         resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n267:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n268:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n269:         resources: [\"pods\"]\n270:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Custom ServiceAccount Annotations\n274: \n275: ```yaml\n276: controllerManager:\n277:   serviceAccount:\n278:     annotations:\n279:       eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n280:       custom.annotation: custom-value\n281: ```\n282: \n283: ## Troubleshooting\n284: \n285: ### Permission Denied Errors\n286: \n287: If you see 403 Forbidden errors:\n288: \n289: 1. Verify ServiceAccount is bound to correct Role/ClusterRole:\n290:    ```bash\n291:    kubectl get rolebindings,clusterrolebindings -n agentcube\n292:    ```\n293: \n294: 2. Verify Role/ClusterRole has required rules:\n295:    ```bash\n296:    kubectl get roles,clusterroles -o yaml\n297:    ```\n298: \n299: 3. Verify ClusterRoleBinding references correct namespace:\n300:    ```bash\n301:    kubectl get clusterrolebinding agentcube-workload-manager -o yaml\n302:    ```\n303: \n304: ### Test Failures\n305: \n306: **Unit test failures:**\n307: - Check Helm template syntax: `helm template agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube`\n308: - Verify values.yaml configuration\n309: - Check for duplicate resource names\n310: \n311: **Integration test failures:**\n312: - Ensure kubectl is configured correctly: `kubectl cluster-info`\n313: - Verify AgentCube is deployed: `kubectl get deployments -n agentcube`\n314: - Check ServiceAccount exists: `kubectl get serviceaccounts -n agentcube`\n315: - Verify RBAC resources exist: `kubectl get roles,clusterroles -n agentcube`\n316: \n317: **Security test failures:**\n318: - Review wildcard permissions found\n319: - Check ServiceAccount annotations\n320: - Verify automountServiceAccountToken settings\n321: \n322: ## Best Practices\n323: \n324: 1. **Principle of Least Privilege**: Grant only necessary permissions\n325: 2. **No Wildcards**: Avoid wildcard `*` verbs unless absolutely necessary\n326: 3. **Namespace Isolation**: Use namespace-scoped permissions where possible\n327: 4. **Custom Rules**: Document reason for each custom permission\n328: 5. **Regular Audits**: Review and audit RBAC configurations regularly\n329: 6. **ServiceAccount Tokens**: Consider disabling automount when not needed\n330: \n331: ## References\n332: \n333: - [Kubernetes RBAC Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/)\n334: - [Helm Best Practices](https://helm.sh/docs/chart_best_practices/)\n335: - [AgentCube Design Document](../../design.md)\n336: \n337: ## Contributing\n338: \n339: When adding new RBAC permissions:\n340: \n341: 1. Update the design document\n342: 2. Add corresponding unit tests to `rbac_test.yaml`\n343: 3. Add integration tests to verify permissions work correctly\n344: 4. Update this README with new configuration options\n345: 5. Run all tests to ensure no regressions\n346: \n347: ## License\n348: \n349: Apache 2.0\n\n(End of file - total 349 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# RBAC Tests for AgentCube Helm Chart\n\nThis directory contains comprehensive tests for the RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) configuration of the AgentCube Helm chart.\n\n## Test Structure\n\n```\ntests/\n├── rbac_test.yaml                          # Helm unit tests for RBAC templates\n├── controller-manager_test.yaml           # Controller manager tests\n├── router_test.yaml                        # Router tests\n├── workload-manager_test.yaml             # Workload manager tests\n└── integration/                            # Integration and security tests\n    ├── test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_router_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_controller_manager_permissions.sh\n    ├── test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n    ├── test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n    ├── test_least_privilege.sh\n    ├── test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/README.md","time":{"start":1775882635511,"end":1775882635544}}}}
